The Way to Calvary: A) with stone Cross: 1) Antwerp, Photo Bruckmann, N° 31; 2) Copenhagen, N° 104, purchased 1899 at Brussels signed, wood 120 x 163 (ex. coll. Ruelens, sold Brussels, April 1883); 3) Phot Hens coll. Antwerp, Exh. Antwerp 1930, N° 30, panneau, 116 x 162, signé en bas à gauche: P. Brueghel, 1603; 4) Netherlandish coll. Exh. De Boer A'dam 1934, N° 23, ex coll. Amedée Provoust, Roubaix; [verso] Exh.[?], St. Lucas, Vienna 1935, N° 49 and Brussels 1935, N° 175, panel, 118 x 165 cm; 5) Lord St. Oswald, Phot. Exh. York 1951, N° 10: Lent by the Trustees of the late Lord St. Oswald, Panel 43 x 64 cm (109, 22 x 162, 56 cm) Signed P BRVEGHEL 1602, ex coll. Wyann, Nostell Priory (Brockwell Nostell Priory Catal. 1915, N° 137); 6) Wedewer sale, Lepke, Berlin, 17 March 1908, N° 83 signed, Holz, 120 x 162 cm; B) the same composition without the stone cross: 1) Uffizi, signed, 1559 (sic!)",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
